text: The 2017 Queensland state election was held on 25 November 2017 to elect all 93 members of the Queensland Legislative Assembly. It was conducted by the Electoral Commission of Queensland (ECQ). The incumbent Labor minority government, led by Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk, won a second term in government, opposed by the Liberal National Party (LNP), led by Tim Nicholls. The Labor Party went from a minority government to a majority government at this election. ==References== Category:Elections in Queensland Category:2017 elections Category:2010s in Queensland
title: 2017 Queensland state election
